## 7. User Roles

After login, check `localStorage.getItem("role")` to determine what the user can see.

```javascript
const role = localStorage.getItem("role");

if (role === "ADMIN") { /* show admin dashboard */ }
if (role === "STUDENT") { /* show student dashboard */ }
if (role === "LECTURER") { /* show lecturer portal */ }
```

Use React Router to protect routes:

```javascript
// ProtectedRoute.jsx
function ProtectedRoute({ allowedRoles, children }) {
  const role = localStorage.getItem("role");
  const token = localStorage.getItem("token");

  if (!token) return <Navigate to="/login" />;
  if (!allowedRoles.includes(role)) return <Navigate to="/unauthorized" />;

  return children;
}

// Usage in Router
<Route path="/admin" element={
  <ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={["ADMIN"]}>
    <AdminDashboard />
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

